  <thing id="xGlimpsFlo" name="Glimpse the Flow" description="The Angelounians believe the Kael is immutable even with foreknowledge, and all possess the ability to glimpse the flows of the future. While this affords them many advantages, the ability is far from perfect, as currents of destiny are difficult to interpret. \n\nAs an immediate action 1/day, you may add a +2 insight bonus to attacks, saves, AC, skill checks or damage rolls for 1 round. Unlike most immediate actions, Glimpse the Flow can be used while flat footed to give a bonus to initiative checks, although it does not remove any of the other penalties of being flat footed nor does it allow an Angelounian caught unawares to act in the surprise round. \n\nUnless otherwise noted, this bonus only applies to checks that occur completely during the duration. For example, using Glimpse the Flow to boost your saves would give a bonus on the initial save if you were poisoned during its duration, but not on the secondary save a minute later unless the duration extended that far. Similarly, certain skills that take longer than a round to utilize (such as Craft, Perform, and Diplomacy) only gain the bonus if the duration exceeds the amount of time required for the check." compset="Special">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="1"/>
    <usesource source="LawfulGCus"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="Angelou"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="21000" index="2"><![CDATA[~ Determine the number of charges we have
   var charges as number
     charges = hero.childfound[xGlimpsFlo].field[hTotal].value

~ Count our Farsight feats and assign a bonus
   var bonus as number
       bonus = tagcount[fCategory.Farsight]

~ Figure out our duration
   var duration as number
    if (#hasfeat[fFarsight] + #hasfeat[fIFarsight] + #hasfeat[fGFarsight] = 3) then
          duration = 8
    elseif (#hasfeat[fFarsight] + #hasfeat[fIFarsight] + #hasfeat[fGFarsight] = 2) then
          duration = 4
    elseif (#hasfeat[fFarsight] + #hasfeat[fIFarsight] + #hasfeat[fGFarsight] = 1) then
          duration = 2
    elseif (#hasfeat[fFarsight] + #hasfeat[fIFarsight] + #hasfeat[fGFarsight] = 0) then
          duration = 1
   endif

~ Set our custom description

      field[CustDesc].text = "The Angelounians believe the Kael is immutable even with foreknowledge, and all possess the ability to glimpse the flows of the future. While this affords them many advantages, the ability is far from perfect, as currents of destiny are difficult to interpret. {br}{br}As an immediate action " & charges & "/day, you may add a +" & bonus & " insight bonus to attacks, saves, AC, skill checks or damage rolls for " & duration & " rounds. Unlike most immediate actions, Glimpse the Flow can be used while flat footed to give a bonus to initiative checks, although it does not remove any of the other penalties of being flat footed nor does it allow an Angelounian caught unawares to act in the surprise round. {br}{br}Unless otherwise noted, this bonus only applies to checks that occur completely during the duration. For example, using Glimpse the Flow to boost your saves would give a bonus on the initial save if you were poisoned during its duration, but not on the secondary save a minute later unless the duration extended that far. Similarly, certain skills that take longer than a round to utilize (such as Craft, Perform, and Diplomacy) only gain the bonus if the duration exceeds the amount of time required for the check."

~ Set our name
      field[livename].text = "Glimpse the Flow, " & charges & "/day (Su) "

~ Set our description
      field[xSumm].text = "Immediate action, gain a +" & bonus & " insight bonus to AC or various rolls for " & duration & " rounds"]]></eval>
    <eval phase="UserPostLv" priority="10100"><![CDATA[
~ Boost our tagcount by 2
      var result as number
        result = assign[fCategory.Farsight]
      var result2 as number
        result2 = assign[fCategory.Farsight]

~ Check whether the Improved sight feat, and add 2 tags if so
      var result3 as number
      var result4 as number
    if (#hasfeat[fImpSight] <> 0) then
      result3 = assign[fCategory.Farsight]
      result4 = assign[fCategory.Farsight]
 endif

~ Check whether the Greater sight feat, and add 2 tags if so
      var result5 as number
      var result6 as number
    if (#hasfeat[fGrSight] <> 0) then
      result5 = assign[fCategory.Farsight]
      result6 = assign[fCategory.Farsight]
 endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="xMaskDep" name="Mask Dependant" description="Before the fall, Angelounians were statuesque creatures possessing skin the color of burnished gold and an ethereal beauty surpassing that of the elves. They stood taller than men, with more robust features and great strength coupled with grace. Unfortunately, the Greendeath damaged even the essences of those it touched, and as a result those born of the original 200 bear the same afflictions and deformities as their forebears, leaving them but a shadow of this past vigor. Unfortunately, the imprinting they receive makes them keenly aware of this disparity, causing them to hide their forms behind masks, tightly wrapped bandages, and clothing.\n\nIf an Angelounian is ever significantly exposed (such as by having his mask removed, or going shirtless), the shame and disgust cause them severe discomfort, imposing a -4 morale penalty to attacks, saves, AC and skill checks.\n\nAngelounian masks take up the &quot;Face&quot; magic item slot, and have only two minor powers. The first is the ability to overlay itself with simple, pre-determined glamers. Most creators choose to include no more than a dozen different, highly exaggerated images to represent the major emotions. Switching between them requires nothing more than a thought, and is a free action for the wearer. The second is a strong magical adhesion that keeps the mask properly in place under most mundane conditions. To remove the mask of an unwilling Angelounian a pin must first be achieved, and then a DC20 strength check must succeed. Alternately, the mask can be affected by a targetted dispel magic, although the caster level of the item is equal to it&apos;s creator&apos;s total character level. Should it be suppressed, the mask will fall away unless held in place by hand or a back-up band.\n\nEvery Angelounian knows the minor enchantments necessary to make a simple Angelounian mask, even if they are not a spellcaster. It does however require an appropriately sized piece of wood/porcelain/cloth and 1 day worth of work. To lay further spells upon the mask requires the Craft Wonderous Item feat, and common enchantments include {i}darkvision{/i}, {i}detect{/i} spells, and {i}true seeing{/i}." compset="Special" summary="-4 morale penalty to all checks when unmasked">
    <usesource source="LawfulGCus"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="Angelou"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="fExSight" name="Extra Sight" description="You can use your Glimpse the Flow ability more often than you otherwise could.\n\n{b}Prerequisite{/b}: Angelounian race\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: You can use your Glimpse the Flow two extra times per day.\n\n{b}Normal{/b}: Angelounians without the Extra Sight feat can use Glimpse the Flow once per day.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects stack." compset="Feat" summary="Gain two extra uses per day of Glimpse the Flow">
