  <thing id="fShapeFlow" name="Shape the Flow" description="You cause a ripple in the flows of Fate, subtly shifting them in favor of your own spell&apos;s success.\n\n{b}Benefit{/b}: By expending one use of your Glimpse the Flow ability, you can add 1/2 of your normal bonus to the save DCs of spells from your chosen school. This is a swift action and the bonus applies to all spells cast over the normal duration of Glimpse the Flow, even if the effects of the spells last longer.\n\nFor example, the caster could use Shape the Flow and boost the DC of his {i}major image{/i} spell for as long as he maintained concentration. If his enemies interact with the illusion 1 hour later, they will still have to pass the increased save DC.\n\n{b}Special{/b}: You can gain this feat multiple times. Its effects do not stack. Each time you take the feat, it applies to a new school of magic to which you already have applied the Spell Focus feat." compset="Feat" summary="Use Glimpse the Flow to add 1/2 normal bonus to DCs of chosen school">
    <usesource source="LawfulGCus"/>
    <tag group="fShowWhat" tag="FocSchools"/>
    <tag group="fSelFrom" tag="Hero"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
    <tag group="BonusFor" tag="Wizard"/>
    <tag group="fCategory" tag="Farsight"/>
    <exprreq message="Glimpse the Flow required."><![CDATA[hero.childfound[xGlimpsFlo].tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <prereq message="Spell Focus required.">
