  <thing id="lBoulmauka" name="Boulmaukan" description="Boulmaukan is the lingua franca of more than half the world. It is analagous to Common, but spoken among the various indiginous tribes and peoples rather than the descendants of Ansalonian colonists. Many traders that travel between the groups speak both, and widely traveled adventurers also often find it convienant to know at least a smattering of each.\n\nIt is derived from Balakan, the language originally spoken in Za&apos;angi, the first boulmaukan kingdom." compset="Language">
