  <thing id="iClawCharo" name="Claws of Charon" description="A living symbiote that lives off the kills of it&apos;s master, the trials that Fai&apos;lon went through to recieve this boon are likely unspeakable.\n\nCharon&apos;s claws are reach weapons that can be used against adjacent foes without penalty. They function as a part of the wearer&apos;s body, effectively becoming natural weapons and so cannot be disarmed, although they can be sundered (hardness 5, Hp 25). If sundered, they cannot be used to attack for 1d4+2 rounds while they regenerate their structure. The claws do not hinder fine manipulations such as spellcasting, but are too bulky to allow the wearing of a shield. They can be affected by either magic weapon or magic fang spells.\n\nAs a full round action, the claws can extend and make a single attack against a target up to 120 ft away. Treat this as a ranged attack." compset="MagicWep">
